1. Crate vpc, public subnet and private subnet, attach ig and create public and private route table, don't create NAT gateway.

2. create 1 public ec2 server on public and 1 private ec2 server on private subnet

3. Create IAM role and attach to both servers

4. Connect public server and run command AWS S3 ls --> you will get s3 bucket list because of Internet Gateway

5. connect private server and run command AWS S3 ls --> not able to get s3 list because there is no route to travel request.

6. Go to vpc, choose Endpoints and create endpoint --> give name then in services search for s3 and choose com.amazonaws.ap-south-1.s3

7. choose type Gateway, select vpc and select private route table then create endpoint.

8. Then go to private server and run command AWS s3 ls --> you will get the list.

9. You can also choose Interface in service type

10. choose vpc and select private subnet, select security group and create.


